5. Interview Questions We Discussed

Q28: What if Hedge Counterparty Defaults?

Back-to-back TRS:

Client ↔ Barclays ↔ Hedge

If hedge counterparty defaults:

Barclays stops receiving hedge payments.

Barclays still owes client.

Barclays must replace hedge.

Replacement may be expensive.


Main risk:

Counterparty Credit Risk

Mitigation:

IA

VM

Daily margining

Netting agreements

Counterparty limits



---

Q38: Why Use TRS Instead of Repo?

Advantages:

Synthetic Exposure

No need to own asset.

Higher Leverage

More exposure with less capital.

Operational Simplicity

No settlement or custody burden.

Balance Sheet Efficiency

Capital deployed more efficiently.

Access

Exposure to difficult-to-access assets.


---

Q39: Why Use Repo Instead of TRS?

Advantages:

Cheaper Funding

Repo spreads are generally lower.

Ownership

Investor owns the asset.

Transparency

Direct ownership and financing.

Long-Term Holding

Often preferred by traditional investors.


